{{redirect|Gamo language|the Nigerian language|Gamo-Ningi language}} {{Infobox language |name=Gamo-Gofa-Dawro |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region=Omo Region |ethnicity= [[Gamo people]] |speakers={{sigfig|2.016|2}} million |date=2007 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic languages|Omotic]] |fam3=[[North Omotic languages|North Omotic]] |fam4=[[Ometo languages|Ometo]] |fam5=North |script=[[Ethiopic script|Ethiopic]], [[Latin script|Latin]] |lc1=gmv|ld1=Gamo |lc2=gof|ld2=Gofa |lc3=dwr|ld3=Dawro |glotto=dawr1235 |glottorefname=Dawro-Gofa-Gamo }}
'''Gamo-Gofa-Dawro''' is an [[Omotic]] language of the [[Afroasiatic languages|Afroasiatic family]] spoken in the [[Dawro Zone|Dawro]], [[Gamo Gofa Zone|Gamo Gofa]] and [[Wolayita Zone]]s of the [[Southern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples' Region]] in [[Ethiopia]]. Varieties are spoken by the [[Gamo people|Gamo]], [[Gofa people|Gofa]], [[Dawro people|Dawro]]; Blench (2006) and ''Ethnologue'' treat these as separate languages. Dialects of Dawro (Kullo-Konta) are Konta and Kucha.<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed. 2005. ''Ethnologue: Languages of the World''. 15th edition. Dallas: Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref> In 1992, Alemayehu Abebe collected a word-list of 322 entries for all three related dialects.<ref>* Alemayehu Abebe, [http://www.sil.org/silesr/2002/SILESR2002-068.pdf "Ometo Dialect Pilot Survey Report"] SIL Electronic Survey Reports SILESR 2002-068</ref>
