{{Infobox former subdivision |subdivision = Semi-autonomous domain |nation = [[Mughal Empire]] |native_name = سلسله تالپور |conventional_long_name = Talpur dynasty |common_name = Silsila Talpur |year_start = 1783 |year_end = 1843 |today = {{flag|Pakistan}} |p1 = Kalhora dynasty |flag_p1 = |p2 = |flag_p2 = |s1 = Bombay Presidency |flag_s1 = British_Raj_Red_Ensign.svg |s2 = |flag_s2 = |flag = Flag of Talpur Dynasty.gif |image_flag = |image_map = |image_map_caption = |national_anthem = |capital = |government_type = Nobility ([[Mir]]'s) |title_leader = |leader1 = |year_leader1 = |leader2 = |year_leader2 = }}
The '''Talpur dynasty''' ({{lang-ur|'''سلسله تالپور'''}}) ({{lang-sd|'''ٽالپردور'''}}) was a dynasty of the [[Talpur]] tribe that conquered and ruled [[Sindh]], and other parts of present-day [[Pakistan]], from 1783 to 1843.<ref>{{Cite web|title = After Independence in 1947 Development in the History and Archiology of Sindh.htm|url = http://www.panhwar.com/Article162.htm|website = www.panhwar.com|accessdate = 2015-08-01}}</ref> The Talpur army defeated the [[Kalhora Dynasty]] in the [[Battle of Halani]] in 1783 to become rulers of [[Sindh]]. The Talpur dynasty was defeated by the British invaders in 1843 at the [[Battle of Miani]].
